The Kano State government has queried the Emir of Kano Muhammadu Sanusi II on allegations of misappropriation of funds. The Kano State Anti-Corruption and Public Complaint Commission on Monday indicted the emir and recommended his suspension. Mr Sanusi’s chief of staff, Munir Sanusi, who confirmed the development said the state government sought the response of the emir within 24 hours regarding allegations of misappropriation of funds. “We received the query today (Thursday). The state government has demanded the response of His Highness within 24 hours. The council is studying the content,” he told an online platform.